        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. The total amount of waste gypsum in CH in 2014 was of 300 thousand tons (Baudirektion Kanton Zurich 2014). The recycling rate for gypsum in CH is of 3% (Baudirektion Kanton Zurich 2014 and Hincapié 2015). The remaining 97% is split according to the ratio in previous version of ecoinvent, 70% of waste goes to inert material landfill, and 30% goes directly to sanitary landfill.
References:
Baudirektion Kanton Zurich (2014) Substance dossier for gypsum recovery from waste compared to primary production. Retrieved from: &lt;http://www.awel.zh.ch/dam/baudirektion/awel/abfall_rohstoffe_altlasten/abfall/dokumente/urban_mining_stoffdossiers/stoffdossiers_englisch/awel_gypsum_a3_en.pdf.spooler.download.1422525351900.pdf/awel_gypsum_a3_en.pdf&gt;, accessed 4th May 2016
